# AI agent rules pointer (Project Manager)

**Shared facts for every AI agent in this repo live in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).**
Read it before any non-trivial change. It defines:

- Cross-discipline product scope; software/IDE/coding-agent workflows are one vertical, not the boundary
- Stack, directory map, ADR-locked decisions
- Iron Rules (zero silent failures, bridge discipline, schemaVersion, key boundary, static export)
- The single completion gate: `npm run verify:baseline`

Cursor-specific extras live in sibling `.mdc` rules in this directory.

If a Cursor rule appears to contradict `AGENTS.md`, `AGENTS.md` wins — open an ADR
under `docs/architecture/` if intentional deviation is needed.
